<Layout title="Assetgrid.app">
	<main>
		<section class="landing">
			<div class="wrapper grid-parent">
				<div class="grid"></div>
				<div class="title">
					<h1>Control your personal finances</h1>
					<h2>See the big picture with Assetgrid</h2>
					<div class="buttons">
						<a href="/get-started" class="button is-primary">Install now</a>
						<a href="/reference" class="button">Reference</a>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="image">
					<img src="happy-money.svg" />
					<a href="http://www.freepik.com" class="image-attribution">Image by pch.vector / Freepik</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
		<div class="dark-divider"></div>
		<section class="about">
			<div class="wrapper narrow">
				<h2>What is Assetgrid?</h2>
				<p>Assetgrid allows you to collect your personal finances in a single place.</p>
				<p>It does not force you into any specific way of organizing your finances. You shouldn't adapt your economy to the software you use, Assetgrid will adapt to you.</p>
				<p>There's a fine balance between software being powerful and software being easy and intuitive to use.
					To accomplish this Assetgrid is configurable. It may take some time the first time you start up Assetgrid to
					configure it according to how you organize your economy, but you are rewarded for your efforts with a program that is tailored exactly to your needs.</p>
				<p>Most importantly, Assetgrid is open source. This means that you run it on your own server and your data never leaves your control.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="horizontal-columns"></div>
		</section>
		<div class="dark-divider"></div>
		<section class="features">
			<h2>Features</h2>
			<div class="feature">
				<div class="text">
					<h3>Overview</h3>
					<p>See how your net worth develops over time, what you spend your money on, your sources of income or any other statistic you may want to know about your finances.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="image">
					<img src="screenshots/overview.png" />
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="feature">
				<div class="text">
					<h3>Powerful CSV importer</h3>
					<p>Most banks allow exporting your bank statement as a CSV file. Assetgrid has a powerful import tool, which will help you no matter what archaic standard your bank organizes the file in.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="image">
					<img src="screenshots/csv_import.png" />
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="feature">
				<div class="text">
					<h3>Categorize your transactions</h3>
					<p>Understand how you spend or earn your money by organizing it into categories.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="image">
					<img src="screenshots/categories.png" />
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="feature">
				<div class="text">
					<h3>Split transactions</h3>
					<p>Transactions with multiple lines are natively supported by Assetgrid, so you can enter in receipts or invoices without losing any information.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="image">
					<img src="screenshots/split_transaction.png" />
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="feature">
				<div class="text">
					<h3>Search</h3>
					<p>At the core of Assetgrid is our powerful search engine that let's you query your transaction in any way imaginable.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="image">
					<img src="screenshots/search.png" />
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
		<section class="upcoming">
			<div class="wrapper narrow">
				<h2>Upcoming features</h2>
				<p>Assetgrid is still in it's infancy, so it's basic at the moment. But we have a lot planned for the future.</p>
				<p>If you want to help us implement these features faster, please donate on Github (USD) or Patreon (EUR).</p>

